isting approaches to critical security studies inadequately address the textured, contradictory, and often resistant practices of everyday life within societies, Mc Cluskey re-gears securitization theory along anthropological lines and shifts the focus of the investigation onto the "idian realm, where much of the controversy over migration and security plays out. A provocative and original political statement on today's increasingly conservative society, From Righteousness to Far Right presents an astounding new perspective on the recent refugee crises and the acceptance and normalization of far-right and securitarian politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355813740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773558137423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773558137/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles